                    <div class = "textbox">
                        <h1> What is Ultimate Frisbee? </h1>
                        <p> Ultimate frisbee, often referred to as Ultimate, is a non-contact, self-refereed sport played with a flying frisbee disc. Ultimate can be played indoors or outdoors, with the number of players on the court per team changing depending on the location. Ultimate teams range from female or male only, or can be mixed. The aim of the game is to catch the frisbee in a rectangular end zone in order to score points. Games are typically 30-45 minutes long. Since Ultimate is a self-refereed sport, at the end of each game there is a spirit circle where teams congratulate the other team, give a small speech about the game, and introduce themselves to the other team. Afterwards, spirit scores are conducted, where you rate the other team on things such as their attitude towards the game and knowledge of the rules, whilst an MVP male and female is also picked. 
                        </p>
                    </div>
